"title": "5109: Paul, apostle to Gentiles",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5109",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Paul saw his encounter with the risen Christ as a call to apostleship, with a special mission to proclaim the gospel to the Gentile world. Paul's complete dedication to Jesus Christ made his own personal weaknesses a vehicle for the power of God.</p>\n<h2>Paul's calling as an apostle: origins and implications</h2>\n<h3>His calling began with his encounter with the risen Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:15-Gal1:16\">GAL 1:15–1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:3-Acts9:19\">ACT 9:3–9:19</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:6-Acts22:16\">ACT 22:6–22:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:12-Acts26:18\">ACT 26:12–26:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:1\">1CO 9:1</a></p>\n<h3>His calling involved his being sent to the unevangelised Gentile world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:9\">GAL 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:21\">ACT 22:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:18-Rom15:21\">ROM 15:18–15:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:13-2Cor10:16\">2CO 10:13–10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:7-Eph3:9\">EPH 3:7–3:9</a></p>\n<h3>His calling put him under an obligation to preach the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:16\">1CO 9:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:14-Rom1:15\">ROM 1:14–1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:11-2Cor5:14\">2CO 5:11–5:14</a></p>\n<h2>Paul's commitment to his apostolic calling</h2>\n<h3>He supported himself in order to present the gospel free of charge</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:6-1Thess2:9\">1TH 2:6–2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:3-1Cor9:18\">1CO 9:3–9:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:13\">2CO 12:13</a></p>\n<h3>He put the gospel before everything else</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:5\">2CO 4:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:1-Rom9:3\">ROM 9:1–9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:19-1Cor9:23\">1CO 9:19–9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:12-Phil1:26\">PHP 1:12–1:26</a></p>\n<h3>He boasted in his weaknesses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:7-2Cor12:10\">2CO 12:7–12:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:7-2Cor4:10\">2CO 4:7–4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:3-2Cor6:10\">2CO 6:3–6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:21-2Cor11:29\">2CO 11:21–11:29</a></p>\n<h3>He experienced God's power at work through him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:11-2Cor12:12\">2CO 12:11–12:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:6-Acts13:12\">ACT 13:6–13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:11-Acts19:12\">ACT 19:11–19:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:18-Rom15:19\">ROM 15:18–15:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:4-1Cor2:5\">1CO 2:4–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:4-1Thess1:5\">1TH 1:4–1:5</a></p>\n<h3>He had a confident attitude to death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:10-Phil3:11\">PHP 3:10–3:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:6-2Cor5:10\">2CO 5:6–5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:20-Phil1:24\">PHP 1:20–1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:6-2Tim4:8\">2TI 4:6–4:8</a></p>\n<h2>Paul and the example of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>His appeal to Jesus Christ as an example to the churches</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:9\">2CO 8:9</a></strong> <em>Paul here uses the example of Jesus Christ in order to encourage the Corinthians in their giving.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:1-Rom15:3\">ROM 15:1–15:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:5-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:5–2:11</a></p>\n<h3>His own exemplary imitation of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:1\">1CO 11:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:14-1Cor4:17\">1CO 4:14–4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:12-Phil3:17\">PHP 3:12–3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:8-Phil4:9\">PHP 4:8–4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:6-2Thess3:9\">2TH 3:6–3:9</a></p>\n<h3>His sharing of Jesus Christ's sufferings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:24\">COL 1:24</a></strong> <em>Paul is not suggesting here that there is any deficiency in Jesus Christ's atoning sacrifice. Rather, there are some aspects of suffering which Christ could not experience because they arose only as a result of people preaching the message of the cross and suffering because of it.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:5-2Cor1:9\">2CO 1:5–1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:7-2Cor4:12\">2CO 4:7–4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:17\">GAL 6:17</a></p>\n<h2>Paul and the churches</h2>\n<h3>His integrity in dealing with the churches</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:12\">2CO 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:17-Acts20:21\">ACT 20:17–20:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:17\">2CO 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:1-2Cor4:2\">2CO 4:1–4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:10-1Thess2:12\">1TH 2:10–2:12</a></p>\n<h3>His love for the churches</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:8\">PHP 1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:7-2Cor11:11\">2CO 11:7–11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:14-2Cor12:15\">2CO 12:14–12:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:12\">1TH 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>His prayers for the churches</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:2\">1TH 1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:8-Rom1:10\">ROM 1:8–1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:15-Eph1:19\">EPH 1:15–1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:11-2Thess1:12\">2TH 1:11–1:12</a></p>\n<h3>His dependence on the prayers of the churches</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:25\">1TH 5:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:30-Rom15:32\">ROM 15:30–15:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:19-Eph6:20\">EPH 6:19–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:22\">PHM 1:22</a></p>\n<h2>Paul's imagery of apostleship</h2>\n<h3>As Jesus Christ's ambassador</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:20\">2CO 5:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:19-Eph6:20\">EPH 6:19–6:20</a></p>\n<h3>As a builder</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:20\">ROM 15:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:10\">1CO 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>As a farmer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:5-1Cor3:9\">1CO 3:5–3:9</a></p>\n<h3>As a father</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:15\">1CO 4:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:11-1Thess2:12\">1TH 2:11–2:12</a></p>\n<h3>As a mother</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:19\">GAL 4:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:6-1Thess2:7\">1TH 2:6–2:7</a></p>\n<h3>As God's captive</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:9\">1CO 4:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:14-2Cor2:16\">2CO 2:14–2:16</a> <em>Paul portrays God as a victorious Roman general, with himself as a captive, bringing up the rear of the triumphal procession.</em></p>\n<h3>As Jesus Christ's slave</h3>\n<p>The word translated <code>servant'' in these verses commonly meant</code>slave'':\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:1\">ROM 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:5\">2CO 4:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:1\">PHP 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:1\">TIT 1:1</a></p>\n<h2>Paul's successors were to safeguard the truth of the gospel after his death</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:1-2Tim2:2\">2TI 2:1–2:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:13-2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:13–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:10-2Tim4:8\">2TI 3:10–4:8</a></p>",
